  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">South Sudan - Internal Conflict</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Thousands of people have been killed in South Sudan following armed clashes between the government forces and opposition groups. The fighting which began in December 2013 in the capital Juba and quickly spread to neighboruing states seems to be fought along ethnic and tribal lines and comes as a major blow to a nation that only gained independence from Sudan in 2011 following decades of bitter fighting. As of February 2015 nearly 2 million of South Sudan s 11 million people are displaced inside and outside of the country. 2.5 million people are currently food insecure (IPC levels 3 and 4).</narrative>
  </description>
